Using OmniScript with Adobe Experience Manager

Adobe Experience Manager is a web deployment option for OmniScript. AEM can be useful for keeping your OmniScripts in line with your organization's designs and implementing custom elements and behaviors.

Setting Up and Configuring Adobe Experience Manager to use with OmniScript
OmniScript can be deployed to the web using Adobe Experience Manager.
Connecting Salesforce Cloud Services with Adobe Experience Manager
Adding a Local OmniScript Definition to Adobe Experience Manager
Add OmniScript to a Page in Adobe Experience Manager

To obtain a local definition of an OmniScript and store it in Adobe Experience Manager, save the OmniScript JSON locally before loading into AEM. Create a page in AEM that uses OmniScript after confirming its presence in Salesforce or defining it locally.

Reference Local Assets in Adobe Experience Manager
Asset references must be made manually while building an OmniScript.
Creating Custom Angular Templates for Adobe Experience Manager

Custom templates saved in AEM can replace specific instances of elements to tweak display and add functionality.
Creating Custom JavaScript and CSS for Adobe Experience Manager

A clientlib is loaded by the OmniScript components, removing the need for customizations. This clientlib is found at /apps/vloc/clientlibs/ooutCustom.
